# OpenSIPS dispatcher set file
# Format: <setid> <destination> <flags> <priority> <weight> <attrs>
#
# Set 1: B2BUA pool — Asterisk (primary) + FreeSWITCH (backup).
#   priority 0 = highest; OpenSIPS prefers lower priority numbers first.
#   If Asterisk misses 3 consecutive OPTIONS pings it is marked inactive
#   and all new calls go to FreeSWITCH automatically. When Asterisk
#   recovers it re-enters the pool — no operator action required.
#
# Set 2: Canary lane — mirrors set 1 until explicitly overridden.
#   Operator can point set 2 to a staging/canary B2BUA for A/B testing.

# setid  destination              flags  priority  weight
1 sip:127.0.0.1:5070 0 0 100   # Asterisk   (primary)
1 sip:127.0.0.1:5080 0 1 100   # FreeSWITCH (backup, auto-failover)
2 sip:127.0.0.1:5070 0 0 100   # Canary: stable mirror (Asterisk)
2 sip:127.0.0.1:5080 0 1 100   # Canary: backup  mirror (FreeSWITCH)
